OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F419A1783669804
OL,3,CMinister orders research into economic
OL,4,Cbenefits of Irish language in NI
OL,6,FThe Irish language has become a topic
OL,7,Fof heated exchanges at Stormont, with
OL,8,FCommunities Minister Gordon Lyons
OL,9,Fbeing accused of "blocking"
OL,10,Fdevelopment of an Irish language
OL,11,Fstrategy, and him alleging a "co-
OL,12,Fordinated attack" by Sinn Fein on the
OL,13,Fissue.
OL,15,FIrish language commissioner Pol Deeds
OL,16,Fwelcomed the new research, saying its
OL,17,Fcommissioning "is particularly timely
OL,18,Fgiven the enhanced focus on Irish-
OL,19,Flanguage service provision introduced
OL,20,Fthrough the Identity and Language
OL,21,F(Northern Ireland) Act 2022".
OL,26,@qD@ROUqD@[O]sD@^OUtD@QO]tD@\rrwD@^rwyD@
OL,26,AOOU}D@\O]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/7
